if you value your GPA NEVER TAKE ONE OF HER CLASSES, She is very unknowledgeable, always says shes gonna get back to questions but never does because she doesn't know the answer, rellies heavly on her notes to get through the lectures and talks about her dogs WAAAAY too much + 50/50 final
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Test heavy', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Glosses over concepts by saying "blah blah blah". Spends too much time talking about her dogs and personal life. Tells students she will not spend time covering concepts since they are in the textbook and only touches on trivial concepts with surface level explanations. Can't answer students' questions, appears she is not well informed of material.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: One word - awful. Gets sidetracked very easily & is all over the place. Has extreme difficulty teaching psychological concepts and gets a little frustrated when she realizes it. Too many videos shown in class, and way too many hyperlinks to external sources that she chooses to show in class. If you can avoid her, do it.

Loved this class! Connie was so nice and super chill. She made the atmosphere very comfortable and I enjoyed going to class every week! The content was also super interesting and it's not hard to get a good grade as long as you keep up with the readings. If you're looking for a chill D level class, I recommend taking this one with Connie.

No to both commenters, watch the lectures and read the text. The exams have details from both. The textbook can be skimmed but it should be read. I found the final easier because I watched the lectures. It is an easy course, but of course it is easy to do poorly if you don't know the material. Read, watch and get the 90.
Did not attend any lectures... read the textbook and read off lecture slides.

Its disappointing that this class was a requirement for my program bc I would never want to take any class with this prof ever again. Lectures has very little information. prof spends more time making lame jokes than teaching. Youre better off just reading the textbook. Midterms and assignments are easy but the final was UNNECESSARILY challenging.
very rude.

Prof is funny but the class itself is very dry. On top of that, the prof is not very good at explaining concepts. She'll go into something then go off on a tangent and doesn't ever go back to her original thought. She also never finishes a lecture and is disorganized. If you can find lecture notes online and read the textbook, you should be okay.
teacherRatingTags: ['Hilarious', 'Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: As long as you do all the assigned chapter readings it is very easy to do well on the midterm and final. For the final however, some material did come from her lecture slides. Overall both exams were fair.

Worst prof ever. If you don't read the textbook you will not pass. She is terrible at explaining things, and never knows how to answer students' questions without taking a week to think about their questions first. Very disorganized and all over the place. She spends more time going off topic than lecturing at times.

When I picked out get ready to read - I did it because you'll find that the textbook is the best source to study for her exams even better than lectures. You can get more than a 70 with just lecture material.  HERES the great part though: Connie is by far the funniest woman that has walked the earth! I lost 2lbs each class from all the laughing!!

Professor Boudens has fair exams, as long as you read the book and attend lectures. She get's bored quite easily, and so sometimes she starts to do weird things (ex. lie down during lecture). She is somewhat rude to students. In one tutorial that she supervised she did a good job. She could be a bit more organized though. Overall she isn't that bad

rComments: One of the worst profs I've had a UTSC. Very disorganized, unprepared, and dry lectures. The exam will be difficult if you don't take detailed notes during the lectures. I definitely would not recommend taking a course with this prof if you don't have to.

Easy A. She is not organized. She laid on a desk one time and told us she can see the slides better from that angle! However, she did explained the content well and clear. Tutorials are mandatory and helpful, just my TA never reply emails.
Realllllly Bad!
Tutorials are really helpful.

You don't to really study the textboook, but you at least have to read it once. Make sure to study her lecture notes VERY well. Beware: There are 1-3 questions on the midterm and exams are based on the videos or examples she uses in lecture. A final thing, her wording of the questions on the exams is pretty bad sometimes. Her tests are ok though!

Tries to be funny/cool in class. Would be nice if she focused more on material than tangentally joking. Glides over key concepts too quickly. Takes attendance rate personally. Doesn't seem motivated to help students. Acts as if we have it easier than she did. TAs are more helpful.  Take it as an opportunity to improve independent study skills.
Not actually sure that even she knows what her lectures are suppose to be about - but hey, there's lots of videos to watch!

Worst prof I've ever had. Terrible organization. Makes up assignments of the top of her head. Gives little to no information about said assignments or tests or the final for that matter. She can be funny sometimes but I'd take a boring prof that had their stuff together over one who doesn't know how to teach. Doesn't give you feedback on anything.
TEXTBOOK IS KEY! Marks come in VERY late!

V.easy exams, most questions are straight from textbook. She sometimes talks irrelevant stuff during the lectures so I ended up not going to her class. And only about 15%~20% of the questions are from her lectures

Easy A. Read the textbook, focus on the main themes she talks about in lecture. You will do well. Exams were fair, although there were some questions that were worded in a way that was hard to understand. She's funny, course material is interesting, and she cares about her students. Would definitely recommend!

Good prof.. a little unorganized, but she makes an effort and tries to make lectures interesting.  She's pretty entertaining too; funny.  Exams are really fair, textbook and lecture material, no surprises.

She is alright at teaching, sometimes does not know what she is doing, spent half the time reading the textbook, it was so ridicuolous that i dropped the class. Office hours she is not patient, and is very rude to the students
She maybe good at teaching but isnt considerate and patient to hear and help students.
the professor was all over the place, she was unclear and had no idea what was going on

She was amazing. Very funny, great selection of articles and topics for the course. YOU MUST ATTEND LECTURE! The class is participation and assignment based so if you want good marks, you have to work for it. Final exam was lengthy but doable. She should teach more courses

The topic for this course is reallyyy boring but Prof Boudens kept the class entertaining with her jokes. Though to be honest I felt like I didn't learn much from her, but I think it was because there is nothing to teach in this topic... There was no midterm, but the final was HARD. but if you're a good student you'll still do well
great prof. dont underestimate her re exams though. term work is simple. she makes the course interested. very fun to be around and understanding.
